Divers have retrieved the fourth and final body of drowned teenagers at Sea Point in Cape Town. #SAMorning Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The body of a fourth teenager drowned at Sea Point in Cape Town has been recovered. The search resumed early Wednesday morning after being called-off last night. The four teenagers who lost their lives have been identified as foreign nationals from Congo and Burundi. WATCH: CT refugee community warns they'll recover a missing body Cape Town's refugee community had warned they would jump into the water this morning if divers were unable to retrieve the last body. The NSRI says the teens were caught in rip currents when a wave washed over them. Watch the video above for more from Sea Point.